Preheat the #oven{} to 425 degrees. Using your hands, stretch the @pizza dough{10%ounce} out into a rough 1/4-inch-thick rectangle. (HINT: If you have a #rolling pin{} or #wine bottle{}, use it to roll out the dough on a lightly floured surface.) Place onto a lightly oiled #baking sheet{} and prick all over with a #fork{}. Place in the oven for about ~{10%minutes}, until beginning to brown on the edges.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tablespoon} in a large pan over high heat. Season the @chicken breasts{12%ounce} on all sides with @salt{} and @pepper{} before adding it to the pan. Cook ~{4-5%minutes} per side, until cooked through. Remove from the pan and set aside.

Wash and dry all produce. While the chicken cooks, shuck the @corn on the cob{1} and cut the kernels off the cob. Quarter the @grape tomatoes{4%ounce}. Thinly slice the @scallions{2}, keeping the greens and whites separate. Mince the @jalapeño{1}, removing the seeds and ribs if you prefer less heat. Halve the @lime{1}.

Combine the corn, tomatoes, scallion whites, and jalapeño (to taste) in a medium #bowl{}. Toss with a drizzle of oil and a squeeze of lime juice. Season with salt and pepper.

Assemble the pizza: Top the prebaked dough with @cheddar cheese{1%cup} and corn salsa. Thinly slice the chicken and place on top. Drizzle with as much @chipotles in adobo{3.5%ounce}(the spicy sauce inside the can) as you like.

> TIP: Taste the adobo sauce first to decide how much to add.

Return to the oven for ~{5-7%minutes}, until the cheese has melted.

Finish and plate: Cut the summer corn and chicken pizza into squares and sprinkle with scallion greens. Top with more adobo sauce or lime juice, if desired. Enjoy!